@danmane That's correct. The current code works if you load the bytes of a file ahead of time, but would throw an error if you passed in code from a function like `tf.read_file`.

The current game plan is to write a `tf.substr` Op and then utilize it in this function. [Here's that conversation for context.](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/4009#issuecomment-244863602)

Thanks!
